      <unittitle encodinganalog="245">Amos R. Green Papers <unitdate type="inclusive" encodinganalog="245$f" normal="1932/1967">1932-1967</unitdate></unittitle>
      <abstract>Amateur archeologist and historian from Niles (Berrien County), Michigan. Biographical and personal material; correspondence; publications; talks, radio interviews and other public presentations; archeological site notes and reports; research sources and notes; maps; photographs; and files relating to his activities with the southwest chapter, Michigan Archeological Society; contain materials relating to his interest in the archaeology, Indian anthropology, and history of the area around Berrien and Cass Counties; also papers documenting his relationship with professionals in various disciplines at the University of Michigan Museums and elsewhere.</abstract>
