        <scopecontent>
          <p>Publications and Presentations Includes typescripts of Green's formal papers as well as an occasional early draft. Most of these works were later published; all were intended for publication. His paper on the Prillwitz Mammoth apparently engendered so much controversy that he withdrew it voluntarily from publication in the Michigan Archeologist (a "history of this paper" is also included). The reports to the Southwest Chapter of the MAS are less formal and much briefer; some are fragmentary. His informal public presentations included short educational talks, radio interviews, narrated slide presentations, and historic tours, all of which are represented here.</p>
        </scopecontent>
