          <p>The series Archeological Fieldwork: Site Notes And Reports is composed of Green's onsite notes and some brief typed reports. (Other reports are found in the correspondence and presentations series.) The notes are usually in pencil and rather fragmentary or cryptic, but some include maps, sketches, and diagrams. The dates for much of the work are unknown, and many of the sites are not referred to distinctly in Green's correspondence--they may represent work done before 1940, perhaps as early as the 1910s.</p>
